Business Brief -- Esterline Technologies Corp.:
   Net Income Tumbles 75%,
   Sending Stock Down $3.50
In New York Stock Exchange trading yesterday, Esterline
dropped $3.50 to $12.125.
   Esterline, a Bellevue, Wash., maker of automation
equipment, quality-control instrumentation, and other gear,
cited depressed electronics and automotive markets. Although
the company said its aerospace and defense business showed
improved sales and earnings.
   According to a Zacks Investment survey, analysts expected
Esterline to earn in the range of 25 cents to 37 cents a
share.